    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="678"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d678">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/708</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>His Majesty’s Government [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] has received instructions
                    to inform the United States Government with a view to avoiding possible
                    misconception that the fact that Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HA1"
                        >Henderson</persName> is accompanying the Russian and English Socialist
                    delegates to Rome and Paris does not in any way commit His Majesty’s Government
                    to any decisions that may be arrived at by the Socialist conferences in those
                    Capitals nor to the general policy which was proposed at the Socialist
                    conference at Stockholm.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 1, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
